OL,6,F"I will never forget what I saw inside
OL,7,Fthat building that day, so I cannot
OL,8,Fbegin to imagine how my daughter will
OL,9,Fever be able to process it.
OL,11,F"I was one of the first on the scene
OL,12,Fand witnessed things no one should
OL,13,Fever see. Despite everything, I still
OL,14,Fconsider us lucky ` lucky that she
OL,15,Fcame home to us.
OL,17,F"But the wounds we carry, hers, mine
OL,18,Fand our family's are invisible and
OL,19,Flifelong."
